# Commits to skip when running `git blame`, so a sweeping reformat doesn't
# obscure who actually wrote each line.
#
# Enable locally (once per clone):
#     git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# Only list commits that are PURELY formatting — a Prettier run and nothing
# else. A commit that also moves, adds, or edits code must NOT go here: blame
# would skip past the real authorship of that code and attribute it to whatever
# happened to precede it.
#
# To make a listed commit, do the reformat on its own:
#     npm run format && git commit -am "style: apply prettier"
#
# ── entries ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (none yet)
#
# Deliberately NOT listed: 64fff74 "Restructure frontend, add type-checking,
# tests, linting and CI". That commit applied Prettier across the tree, but it
# also created 20 modules, deleted 54 files and changed behaviour, so ignoring
# it would hide real authorship rather than reveal it. The restructured code
# legitimately originates there.
